member.example:
The following is an example of a method, which can be passed as the  parameter
to the setTestIsReadonly method.
This method returns true, if the specified 
instance is an anchor element, to prevent the end user from editing the contents of any anchor element.

 static bool isAnchorTag(IDomNode domNode)
 {
     if (domNode.nodeType == DomNodeType.Element)
     {
         IDomElement domElement = (IDomElement)domNode;

         //return true iff the node is an anchor tag
         if (domElement.tagName == "a")
         {
             return true;
         }
     }
     return false;
 }

member.summary:
The layout name can be used as shown in the following example, and as described in http://www.tutorialspoint.com/css/css_paged_media.htm

<style type="text/css">
<!--
@page { size : portrait }
@page rotated { size : landscape }
table { page : rotated }
-->
</style>

member.remarks:
The contents of this element correspond to just the operator term clause within the following lines of the CSS grammar:
expr : term [ operator term ]* ;
The contents of the operator element correspond to the following lines of the CSS Grammar:
operator : '/' S* | COMMA S* | ;

The contents of this element correspond to just the combinator simple_selector clause within the following lines of the CSS grammar:
selector : simple_selector [ combinator simple_selector ]* ;
The contents of the combinator element correspond to the following lines of the CSS Grammar:
combinator : PLUS S* | GREATER S* | S ;

member.summary:
Gets the value used for the  property, if the fullPathOfLogFile value isn't set explicitly.


The implementation of this method is as follows:

public string defaultPathOfLogFile
{
    get
    {
        string commonUserFolder = Environment.GetFolderPath(Environment.SpecialFolder.ApplicationData);
        string path = commonUserFolder + @"\" + "ModelText.exception.txt";
        return path;
    }
}


On a Windows Vista machine, the resulting path is something like C:\Users\[YourUserName]\AppData\Roaming\ModelText.exception.txt.
